<br>
WIS clearly is even more powerful now with our simply amazing ae heal and the 255 wis cap.<br>
<br>
Resists are necessary to mitigate ae spells. Especially since buffs will probably be dispelled after a few minutes.<br>
<br>
HP of course means you last longer.<br>
<br>
<br>
SO....<br>
<br>
<br>
Assuming your role is to stay alive, do some damage and now with a good ae heal to keep your group alive.  How much wis/resists/hp would you trade for one of the other 3?<br>
<br>
Would you consider maxing wis if your group had no cleric and hiding behind a wall to avoid ae and simply medding and healing group with ae heal? Probably not, but its an option if you have alot of melees in group. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uchronnos1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chronnos1</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/21/01 3:54:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13558.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.kmrcs.com/eqcleric/gallery/Prexus/Chronnos.jpg Width=175 Height=127></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HP vs resists vs wis vs NTOV Dragons</span><hr size=1> My general rule is Hp/sta &gt; resist &gt; mana/wisdom<br>
<br>
Fully raid buffed Im sitting at 5500-5700 hps, 175-210 to 3 resists, and ~150-175wis (with about 450 in mana items). I can cast the AE heal roughly 4 times, and barely ever die in Ntov. I end up playing cleric in group while the cleric is in the main tank CH order, and on a Vulak fight I go oom usually 10mins into the fight(fight lasts ~12mins)<br>
<br>
I feel that wisdom/ mana isnt an important stat if you are dead, so maximize your ability to live 1st and then work on that as a 2ndary stat<br>
<br>
<br>
